### Problem description

Hi, i'm testing creating a module for easily including the ability of executing Termux commands from my apps, but i have run in a curious problem.

If follow the RUN_COMMAND tutorial, that is, creating an app that executes a command from the MainActivity class, all works as expected (while debugging, the breakpoint inside onHandleIntent function is hit) but when i try in other app where the Termux functionality is inside of another module (the library all the other apps will include to make use of Termux), the breakpoint is never reached.

And without throwing erros in Logcat!

### Steps to reproduce the behavior.

I'm doing the testing in my Redmi Note 8, an Android 11 device.

This is the TermuxModule manifest:


>     <queries>
>         <package android:name="com.termux" />
>     </queries>
> 
>     <application>
>         <service android:name=".TermuxResultService" />
>     </application>
> 
>     <uses-permission android:name="com.termux.permission.RUN_COMMAND"  />

The IntentService code is the same of the tutorial.
I put the breakpoint here:


> @Override
>     protected void onHandleIntent(@Nullable Intent intent) {
>         **if (intent == null) return;**
> 
>         Log.d(LOG_TAG, PLUGIN_SERVICE_LABEL + " received execution result");
> 
>         final Bundle resultBundle = intent.getBundleExtra(TERMUX_APP.TERMUX_SERVICE.EXTRA_PLUGIN_RESULT_BUNDLE);
>         if (resultBundle == null) {
>             Log.e(LOG_TAG, "The intent does not contain the result bundle at the \"" + TERMUX_SERVICE.EXTRA_PLUGIN_RESULT_BUNDLE + "\" key.");
>             return;
> }


And this is the TermuxModule code:


> package me.ariaththesage.android.libs.termuxmodule.termuxmodule;
> 
> import android.app.PendingIntent;
> import android.content.Context;
> import android.content.Intent;
