>     protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
>         super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
>         setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
> 
>         Termux.ExecuteCommand (getApplicationContext(),"uname -a");
>     }
> }


I also put a breakpoint at "Log.i("TERMUX_COMMAND_RESULT", resultsServiceIntent.getStringExtra("STDOUT"));" and at "appContext.startForegroundService(termuxRequest);".

When the debugging stops at "startForegroundService", and i click "Continue" in Android Studio, the debugger stops at "Log.i("TERMUX_COMMAND_RESULT", resultsServiceIntent.getStringExtra("STDOUT"));" insted the other line in the IntentService.

I suppose i'm doing something wrong, but i would love to know what...

### What is the expected behavior?

I would say "It should work" XD .

The module purpose is execute a command line in the background calling Termux module and retrieve the results (stdout and exit code).

### System information

* Termux application version: 0.118.0
* Android OS version: 11
* Device model: Redmi Note 8 (rooted)
